A value of 0 is required for data for 2007 forward (for FDIUS) for 2009 forward (for USDIA).', 'Classification is a string used to obtain data that is broken down by both country and industry for either inward or outward data.  It can take one of four possible values:', "Country is usually a number.  Because there can be several variants of a country's name, three-digit numeric codes are used to select countries.  A full list of these codes is available near the end of this document or can be obtained by using the GETPARAMETERVALUES method.  To obtain data for every country (including the all-country total) separately use 'all'.  To obtain a total for all countries, use '0000'.   To obtain data for multiple countries, each country code should be listed and separated by a comma.", "Industries are denoted by four-digit codes. It represents the firm's contribution to a country's gross domestic product, which is the value of goods and services produced by labor and property located in the country.  Compared to sales, value added is a preferable measure of production because it indicates the extent to which a firm's sales result from their own production rather than from production that originates elsewhere, whereas sales data do not distinguish between these two sources of production.  Value added can be measured as gross output minus intermediate inputs; alternatively, it can be measured as the sum of the costs incurred (except for intermediate inputs) and the profits earned in production.
